)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MessageEvent\"><code>MessageEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/MessagePort\"><code>MessagePort</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/Navigator\"><code>Navigator</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PageTransitionEvent\"><code>PageTransitionEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Plugin\"><code>Plugin</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PluginArray\"><code>PluginArray</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PopStateEvent\"><code>PopStateEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PromiseRejectionEvent\"><code>PromiseRejectionEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RadioNodeList\"><code>RadioNodeList</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/ValidityState\"><code>ValidityState</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/Window\"><code>Window</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>\n\n<p>A propriedade&nbsp;<strong><code>HTMLElement.offsetHeight</code></strong> é somente leitura e retorna um valor do tipo inteiro a altura de um elemento incluindo &nbsp;padding-top+padding-bottom+border-top+border-bottom.</p>\n\n<p>Typically, an element's <code>offsetHeight</code> is a measurement in pixels of the element's CSS height, including border, padding and&nbsp;the element's horizontal scrollbar (if present, if rendered).</p>\n\n<p>For the document body object, the measurement includes total linear content height instead of the element's CSS height. Floated elements extending below other linear content are ignored.</p>\n\n<div class=\"note notecard\" id=\"sect1\">\n<p>This property will round the value to an integer. If you need a fractional value, use <a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/Element/getBoundingClientRect\"><code>element.getBoundingClientRect()</code></a>.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax_and_values","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\">var <em>intElemOffsetHeight</em> = <em>element</em>.offsetHeight;</pre>\n\n<p><em>intElemOffsetHeight</em> is a variable storing an integer corresponding to the offsetHeight pixel value of the element. The offsetHeight property is read-only.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example","title":"Example","isH3":false,"content":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;  <img alt=\"Image:Dimensions-offset.png\" class=\"internal\" src=\"/@api/deki/files/186/=Dimensions-offset.png\" loading=\"lazy\"></p>\n\n\n<p>The example image above shows a scrollbar and an offsetHeight which fits on the window. However, non-scrollable elements may have large offsetHeight values, much larger than the visible content. These elements are typically contained within scrollable elements; consequently these non-scrollable elements may be completely or partly invisible, depending on the scrollTop setting of the scrollable container.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specification","title":"Specification","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Specification</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Comment</th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://drafts.csswg.org/cssom-view/#dom-htmlelement-offsetHeight\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">CSS Object Model (CSSOM) View Module<br><small lang=\"pt-BR\">The definition of 'offsetLeft' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-wd\">Rascunho atual</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"notes","title":"Notes","isH3":true,"content":"<p><code>offsetHeight</code> is a property of the DHTML object model which was first introduced by MSIE. It is sometimes referred to as an element's physical/graphical dimensions, or an element's border-box height.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"browser_compatibility","title":"Compatibilidade com navegadores","isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\"><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/mdn/browser-compat-data\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Estamos convertendo nossos dados de compatibilidade para o formato JSON</a></strong>.\n            Esta tabela de compatibilidade ainda usa o formato antigo,\n            pois ainda não convertemos os dados que ela contém.\n            <strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Structures/Compatibility_tables\" class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\">Descubra como você pode ajudar! (en-US)</a></strong></div>\n\n<div class=\"htab\" id=\"sect3\">\n    <a id=\"AutoCompatibilityTable\" name=\"AutoCompatibilityTable\"></a>\n    <ul>\n        <li class=\"selected\"><a href=\"#compat-desktop\">Desktop</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"#compat-mobile\">Dispositivo móvel</a></li>\n    </ul>\n</div><p></p>\n\n<div id=\"compat-desktop\">\n<table class=\"compat-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th>Feature</th>\n   <th>Chrome</th>\n   <th>Firefox (Gecko)</th>\n   <th>Internet Explorer</th>\n   <th>Opera</th>\n   <th>Safari (WebKit)</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td>Basic support</td>\n   <td><span style=\"color: #888\" title=\"Please update this with the earliest version of support.\">(Yes)</span></td>\n   <td>31</td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"compat-mobile\">\n<table class=\"compat-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th>Feature</th>\n   <th>Android</th>\n   <th>Android Webview</th>\n   <th>Firefox Mobile (Gecko)</th>\n   <th>Firefox OS</th>\n   <th>IE Mobile</th>\n   <th>Opera Mobile</th>\n   <th>Safari Mobile</th>\n   <th>Chrome for Android</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td>Basic support</td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span style=\"color: #888\" title=\"Please update this with the earliest version of support.\">(Yes)</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span title=\"Compatibility unknown; please update this.\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 153, 0);\">?</span></td>\n   <td><span style=\"color: #888\" title=\"Please update this with the earliest version of support.\">(Yes)</span></td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n\n<p>In compliance with the specification, this property will return <code>null</code> on Webkit if the element is hidden (the <code>style.display</code> of this element or any ancestor is <code>\"none\"</code>) or if the <code>style.position</code> of the element itself is set to <code>\"fixed\"</code>.</p>\n\n<p>This property will return <code>null</code> on Internet Explorer (9) if the <code>style.position</code> of the element itself is set to <code>\"fixed\"</code>. (Having <code>display:none</code> does not affect this browser.)</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See Also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/clientHeight\"><code>Element.clientHeight</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/scrollHeight\"><code>Element.scrollHeight</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/HTMLElement/offsetWidth\"><code>HTMLElement.offsetWidth</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CSS_Object_Model/Determining_the_dimensions_of_elements\" title=\"en/Determining_the_dimensions_of_elements\">Determining the dimensions of elements</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions//hh781509(v=vs.85)\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">MSDN: Measuring Element Dimension and Location</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax_and_values"},{"text":"Example","id":"example"},{"text":"Specification","id":"specification"},{"text":"Compatibilidade com navegadores","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See Also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"A propriedade HTMLElement.offsetHeight é somente leitura e retorna um valor do tipo inteiro a altura de um elemento incluindo  padding-top+padding-bottom+border-top+border-bottom.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"HTMLElement.offsetHeight","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"HTMLElement.offsetHeight","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"element.offsetHeight","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"HTMLElement.offsetHeight","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"HTMLElement.offsetHeight","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"HTMLElement.offsetHeight","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"pt-br/web/api/htmlelement/offsetheight","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/pt-br/web/api/htmlelement/offsetheight/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/pt-BR/docs/Web","title":"Tecnologia Web para desenvolvedores"},{"uri":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API","title":"APIs da Web"},{"uri":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/HTMLElement","title":"HTMLElement"},{"uri":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/API/HTMLElement/offsetHeight","title":"HTMLElement.offsetHeight"}],"pageTitle":"HTMLElement.offsetHeight - APIs da Web | MDN","noIndexing":false}}